Task 1

Firstly, the given datasets are examined and prepared to be used in the following steps.

The column score splitted into two (i.e. HomeGoals and AwayGoals) and new columns are converted to numeric values.

matches[,c("HomeGoals","AwayGoals"):= tstrsplit(score,':')]

matches$HomeGoals <- as.numeric(matches$HomeGoals)
matches[,AwayGoals:= as.numeric(AwayGoals)]

Additionally, IsOver and Result columns are created.

matches[,TotalGoals:= HomeGoals + AwayGoals]
matches[,IsOver:=0]
matches[TotalGoals>2,IsOver:=1]

matches[,Result:=0]
matches[HomeGoals>AwayGoals,Result:=1]
matches[HomeGoals<AwayGoals,Result:=2]

Part 4

The noisy image has been turned into a single channel grayscale image.

grayimage<-channel(image_noisy,"gray")

In order to apply PCA, patches extracted from the image by sliding a 3x3 window and they all stored as a vector length of 9.

y <- 200-2
x <- 1:y
n <- y*y

A <- as.data.frame(matrix(nrow=n,ncol=9))

count= 1
  for (i in x){
    for(j in x){
      A[count,] <- (grayimage[i:(i+2),j:(j+2)])
      count=count+1
    }
  }

b

Image can be reconstructed using components of PCA (See Appendix A).

Here is the image obtained by combining all three components:

APPENDIX A

afterPCA <- function(
  matAdjust = 'Centered matrix',
  meanList = 'List of column means of original (unadjusted) matrix',
  eigenList = 'List of eigenvalues and eigenvectors of adjust matrix covariance matrix',
  n = 'selected PC\'s',
  specific_select = 'If False: n == 1:n, if True: just n\'th columns') {
  
  if (!specific_select) n <- 1:n
  
  t(eigenList$vectors[,n] %*% (t(eigenList$vectors[,n]) %*% t(matAdjust))) + t(matrix(meanList, nrow = nrow(matAdjust), ncol = ncol(matAdjust)))
}


showMatrix <- function(x, ...) image(t(x[nrow(x):1,]), xaxt = 'none', yaxt = 'none',...)

reconstMatrix <- afterPCA(
  matAdjust = apply(grayimage, 2, function(i) i - mean(i)),
  meanList = apply(grayimage, 2, mean),
  eigenList = pca,
  n = 3,
  specific_select = FALSE
)

par(mfrow = c(1,2))
showMatrix(grayimage, main = 'Original Image')
showMatrix(reconstMatrix, main = 'First 3 PC\'s')
